																		GoI Idea: Anomalous Protectors Patrol
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/daniel-stell" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5711885); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=5711885&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610162188" alt="Daniel Stell" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=5711885)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/daniel-stell" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5711885); return false;" >Daniel Stell</a></span> <span class="odate time_1574537337 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">23 Nov 2019 19:28</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4430146">
									

<p>Description: APP (Anomalous Protectors Patrol) is essentially an organization of anomalous humans who use their powers to protect people who don't have powers, like superheroes. The GoI was started in the late '60s by eight individuals with anomalous properties, who are known as the Champion's League. Many members have arcane &amp; occult abilities and some even have reality-bending capabilities. The organization poses no threat to the Foundation itself, but the Foundation still keeps a close eye on them just to make sure.</p>
<p>I know about the whole X-Man syndrome that people don't like, but I still feel like this organization's existence would make sense in the SCP universe because some people would try to use this new &quot;gift&quot; to help people around the world.</p>
<p>Any thoughts?</p>

							</div>

								
					
